**Idea:**
We create a `new_head` which is previous to the regular head. This makes it super easy to remove nodes in the beginning of the list.
Then, each time we find a node with value equals `val`, we just make a "bypass" and link the previous node to the next one.
We save in `tmp` a pointer to the removed node to be able to free the memory.

**Time Complexity:** O(n)
**Space Complexity:** O(1)
```
class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* removeElements(ListNode* head, int val) {
        ListNode* new_head = new ListNode(-1), *tmp;
        new_head->next = head;
        head = new_head;

        while (head->next) {
            if (head->next->val == val) {
                tmp = head->next;
                head->next = head->next->next;
                delete tmp;
            }
            else head = head->next;
        }

        return new_head->next;
    }
};
```
